summary: It’s not queer baiting if the subtext is there in the original work and we’ve been told the possibility of an explicit on screen...
body:
It’s not queer baiting if the subtext is there in the original work and we’ve been told the possibility of an explicit on screen gay relationship doesn’t exist, and it would not be true to the canon if there was one. Please stop clogging my happy place with your complaints.

That said: in my opinion the story is not about the boys falling in love anyway, that is a realization that happens post the events of book with the development and acknowledgement of buried feelings and both David and Michael get that and so far seem to pull it off perfectly.

Also, also, I’m well aware some of you are using queer baiting in a light hearted and sarcastic type of manner but I see many people who def. don’t mean it that way.

summary:
Ok, remember when Neil said in that interview about David’s contacts 
that in the Eden scenes they had him wear ones that...
caption:
Ok, remember when Neil said in that interview about David’s contacts that in the Eden scenes they had him wear ones that covered the whole eye, not just the pupils? And then later, when Crowley had “acclimated to earth” I think is how he put it, they switched them out for ones that covered only his pupils, like a more normal human eye.

Now take a good look at these screencaps. I don’t think Crowley’s eyes are gonna start glowing red in the burning Bentley scenes; I think they’re gonna go back to exactly that pre-Earth-life way they used to be.
